You are contributing to the Educari frontend (educari-2027-front).

**Before any action, read AGENTS.md in the repo root.** It is the single source of truth.

The backend (Laravel API) lives in a separate repository:
https://github.com/fabiotgk/educari-2027-infra

The AGENTS.md of the backend is the **primary** source of conventions
(commit style, multi-tenancy rules, language rules, etc.).

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack) + React 19 + TypeScript 5
- Tailwind CSS 4 + shadcn/ui (copied components, not a dependency)
- TanStack Query v5 + Zustand
- next-auth v5 (OAuth client → Laravel Passport)
- framer-motion (sparingly)
- React Hook Form + Zod
- Vitest + Testing Library

## Key rules

1. PT-BR everywhere for human-facing text (commits, PRs, UI, errors).
   English in technical identifiers (components, hooks, files).
2. Co-Author commits with: `Co-Authored-By: Ailiv <naoresponda@ailiv.com.br>`
   — never Claude/GPT/Cursor/Cline/Llama/Kimi.
3. Multi-tenancy aware: every data-consuming component uses
   `useTenant()` hook. Check `hasFeature()` before rendering modules.
4. No hard-coded tenant logic (`if (slug === 'mariana')`) — use
   feature flags + theme + glossary.
5. Server Components by default. `'use client'` only when necessary.
6. TypeScript strict. No `any`. Use `unknown` + narrowing.
7. shadcn/ui copy-paste, not modify in place without documenting.

→ Open AGENTS.md now.
